text: unusual seeing lightening in the morning, the storm seems to be towards cleveland but could see a number of ground lightening strikes with thunder taking a number of seconds to be heard from the distance. on the edge of blue sky coming from greenslopes now.

paper wasps have made a nest outside the window upstairs lounge, luckily it is on the other side of the flywire screen, something long would be required to remove it from outside but wouldn't be wise to attack the nest as they would get aggressive and try to sting.

raven st connects onto prout st that gets back onto boundary rd to get back onto cavendish rd, so cuts out the lights at the old cleveland and boundary rd intersection that can queue until the lights change and wasn't out of the way to get home.

i had a psychologist appointment in carina yesterday and on the way home went left down raven st off old cleveland and apart from a sign out the front doesn't show the enormity of the loss of life in such a quiet street.

they have started at the western end of the street a couple of houses down and being in the middle of the townhouse complex insulated either side can only hear the works outside very slightly at times and the high fan mode on the air conditioner running is loud.

urban utilities have needed to dig up the road for access to the pipes and have closed the road, which isn't possible during school hours. there was some inaccurate information that circulated when it was thought they were going to turn the water off tonight.

police shooting was directly inline with my former solicitors firm at 130 mary st. the response was overkill to mistake mental illness for terrorism to just shoot to kill and at close range should be aiming at stomach and not the chest as its less likely to kill.
it would be far less costly for queensland to have the death penalty than to have mandatory life sentences for murder with lengthy minimums. life sentences just keep filling up the prison population.

queensland police have become more and more trigger happy in recent years. the shooting on mary st was just outside my former solicitors office, police didn't seem to even try using a taser and the number of shots resembled more of an execution than self defence.

the asbestos piping is being replaced and the water will be turned off at night from 9pm to 5am due to living next to schools. it is because of the asbestos risks to kids during school hours that urban utilities cannot remove the pipes during the day.

due to the length of my fast and going in later at 11:30am rather than 7am, phentermine would work as an appetite suppressant not to feel hungry. a script for duromine 15mg 30 tablets is $108.50 at chemist warehouse and does not look like a generic is available.

my second endoscopy has been scheduled for thursday march 12th, but i just hope i am not too drowsy to see the start of the  season, so will look at getting medications to counteract the sedation medication. one stimulant duromine costs over $100 per script.

luckily i had the anz internet banking on my phone to shift money into my other account to make a $40 withdrawal using my other card. the machine had been playing up and i inserted it after the tap and pin malfunctioned.

fucking anz atm was faulty in the queen st mall, it mistakenly swallowed my card after believing it was being used unauthorised trying to make a cash withdrawal and will have to contact anz lost and stolen cards later on to sort it out.

there are white paint marks along the street where qld urban utilities are going to be working to replace pipes from tomorrow. i had initially thought it might have been about the fire hydrants requiring servicing but had more paint markings than blue reflectors.

i have a 3d lenticular cover for the xbox one remake of resident evil 2 that goes up to 4k resolution and the classification got raised to r18+ from ma15+, as it was on ps1 and gamecube in standard definition when there was then no r18+ for games.

i have an alfred hitchcock 14 movie blu ray box set that has a lenticular or 3d look cover, pre 1971 the highest classification was equivalent to an m today with the film censorship board taking an approach to cut or censor than classify films as restricted.

one of the centacare workers i had today, while another had training went to school locally at clairvaux mackillop college on klump rd, is indigenous and she had pethidine during her kids births. she helped me to get rid of empty pill casings and boxes on my desk.

qld urban utilities are doing work around the driveway and nature strip to replace an old pipe, but will be out with a drs appointment on friday morning so won't have a noise issues. i should know in the next week or so when my 2nd endoscopy will be scheduled.

pethidine generally comes as a 50mg/ml in contrast the fentanyl equivalent is only 50mcg/ml, i am more suited to the weaker phenylpiperidine class opiates that include tramadol and tapentadol. buprenorphine and fentanyl due to potency have increased side effects.

pethidine is traditionally used in obstetrics and gynecology, so might not have it available in the gastroenterology area of the hospital to use during endoscopy as an alternative to fentanyl, but planned ahead could be obtained via script ordered from a pharmacy.

the endoscopy appointments are booked in blocks of around 4 to 6 weeks, so there is enough to plan ahead to prepare. i've asked about the cost pethidine scripts and the 50mg/ml is under $40 for 5 vials at a local discount pharmacy, it is non pbs subsidized.

i just hope it wasn't mistaken for the anzac day week in april when getting re booked for my endoscopy but it shouldn't do given that it is a saturday this year and that week in march from the 23th to the 27th is a full five day week without any public holidays.

i managed to get through on one of the numbers starting in 3176 to get a re booking for my 2nd endoscopy, i had indicated i was not available in the week from march 23 to 27 when the  is sitting, but i got confused thinking march 25 was anzac day.

julie & julia was example that got changed from m to pg by the classification review board when the f bomb in context was found only to have a mild impact. sleuth and rocketman were downgraded ma15+ to m for respective c bombs.

it was noticeable with the f bomb live during the oscars coverage that was unusually strong for a pg, although until 3pm is still within the m timeslot. australia does need to upgrade the classifications to get a pg-13 type rating between the pg and m.

it has been quite frustrating this morning trying to find the letter that had who i needed to call to rearrange my endoscopy and there is a possibility that the letter may have been accidentally discarded by centacare who now come on a wednesday to help me clean.

my deodorant cans seem to set off the newer photoelectric smoke alarms early in the mornings from time to time, the aerosols contain flammable gas that clouds up in a confined space, but it responds the same way as smoke detected even though nothing is alight.
the deadline should get extended not to have rushed submissions or have instances of not being able to look at different issues around the digital age done more comprehensively.

the consultation white paper on films, computer games and publication classifications is a bit too short setting the 19th of february as the deadline for submissions to be received instead of some time in march or april as it only commenced in january.

i was right about not being able to keep the enrollment below 3300  in 2020 after the smaller cohort graduated in 2019, they will have around 3360 in 2020. it is harder to predict year 7 cohort numbers for 2021 when the new secondary college opens.
the real time live tracker gave me incorrect information that the 170 was going to be delayed up to another 9 minutes towards 9am but turned up 8:53, so was only 4 minutes behind.

traffic is terrible on logan rd around mt gravatt & holland park this morning with the wet weather around. i am waiting for a 170 which will likely have some delays before it turns into marshall rd and reaches the busway.

the communications were likely messages from the depot to drivers on routes with flood prone roads with diversions and road closure information. the alerts signals on radio sounded like the alarm bells when an emergency button inside a lift is mistakenly pressed.

yesterday on the 170, i think was the first time i have ever seen a bus driver put the wipers on their fastest setting, while heading inbound along the busway and the driver was getting emergency communications as it sounded like pressing a lift emergency button.

i would be surprised that it would get up to 29 degrees in brisbane with all the cloud cover and wet weather unless the sun came out for a while to raise the mercury up higher and would be an uncomfortably muggy to be outside, i have an appointment late morning.
council haven't mowed the grass in the park with the ekibin creek overflow running through since all the wet weather recently, some of the grass is knee height or more.

the grass in the park between nursery road and the child care centre has become very overgrown after all the recent rain and while personal training today got a large black ant into my shoe and could feel a sting on my foot and only saw it once i took my shoes off.

legs feel sore today and slept for most of the time in between but i managed to fully complete the yul-yan-man track and was a long walk from there to matthew flinders park, to get more drinking water. then took an uber back to the beerburrum access carpark.

view on the yul-yan-man track yesterday, i struggled a lot with only 3 litres of water, i ran out on the mt beerburrum summit, then a long very steep descent on the rock face that was like mt tibrogargan, after passing the near vertical cliffs enroute to summit.
at glasshouse mountains national park where i have really tested my endurance and scrambling skills along the class 5 yul-yan-man track out in the hot humid sun.

my dentist has referred me to an oral surgeon dr barbara woodhouse who i will see in redcliffe on march 2nd to look at getting my bottom right wisdom tooth out that has roots very close to the nerve due to my tension headaches and recurring streptococcus infection.

i also needed a filling on my back tooth next to the bottom left wisdom tooth which got taken out, that was severely decayed underneath my gum at the roots where the infection affected it and was done on the same day as the 2 extractions under the local anesthesia.

in mid september 2017, i had the strep infection affect the area underneath my gumline, i was in a lot of pain and my dentist dr anne fardoulys put me on the metronidazole, that cleared it before the extractions of both my left wisdom teeth was able to go ahead.

as well as not having family in brisbane to take me home after the procedure being on my own from yesterday to mid february, due to the streptococcus mutans infection that can be very painful at times my 2nd endoscopy at the pa hospital has needed to be postponed.

for the streptoccus mutans, amoxicillin and erythromycin have limited effect by only reducing severity of the infection and not completely killing the bacteria and is why metronidazole is needed to treat it being a gram positive anaerobic infection.

i have got tonsillitis again, which seems to be a recurring anaerobic infection with non-β-hemolytic, streptococcus mutans i have several times a year. my mouth and tongue get very dried out due to my medication and hot weather, this bacteria causes tooth decay.
the  can subpoena the cabinet in confidence material under federal law.
education queensland consulted crown law after the submissions were received but before the decisions were taken to set aside the principals recommendation to exclude me from the particular schools.

part of the classified information, as cabinet in confidence, is likely to include the legal advice that education queensland received, when the appeals against proposals to exclude me from schools raised issues of repeated breaches of the anti discrimination act.

provisions of the royal commissions act 1902 (cth) that allow information to be subpoenaed would override any applicable provision of queensland law, due to s109 of the constitution and the specific queensland law rendered invalid to the extent of inconsistency.

it is possible with the  that due to restrictions my solicitors faced in applying under the foi or freedom of information act that classified queensland cabinet in-confidence information not for release before 2038/2039 could be subpoenaed by the .

it was a bit of an improvement over yesterday morning personal training with the humidity with a breeze coming from time to time. i was wearing thicker cotton clothes yesterday which wasn't so good as i had my other lighter clothes yet to be dried from the wash.

the microphones weren't working before the commercial break with the sound on the signal being vibrations only and cannot hear what is being said . finally able to hear the morning news headlines now.
is having technical issues with the sound this morning, it has gone mostly mute.

i gave the final go ahead today to upload files from earlier legal cases to a database used by the , to analyse for case studies; it's taken a month due to the christmas break and particular protocol the royal commission uses to obtain sensitive information.

i have a lot of endurance despite low blood sugar levels and still managed a hard workout during personal training in the higher humidity and using a 12kg ball for an extended time walking and ball throwing, i have another personal training session tomorrow.

it's mainly a risk in later life to have excessive adrenaline production that could cause a heart attack particularly if i am involved in something that causes acute but severe shock such as a motor vehicle accident, i regularly function with low blood sugar level.

i tested out pico prep for a second time and it does appear that my metabolism is 4 to 6 times slower than average, although i produce excessive amounts of adrenaline, get heart palpitations, tremors and anxiety that can be extreme severe and have hypoglycemia.

the nervous shock type syndrome following the accident is causing a lot more problems for me with an over production of adrenaline which interacts with the noradrenaline from venlafaxine, causing dizziness, tremors and sleeping difficulties.

i was saved from more serious injury due to the roll over protection on the xuv model gators and the worst of it physically was a fractured middle toe on my right root and bad bruising on my big toe on my right foot where i got my foot pinned under the accelerator.

i had an atv accident on sunday on an overgrown trail on a family property in northern nsw, where i failed to see an approaching embankment that i got to much of a run up on the right side and the john deere xuv 560 gator tipped over onto its left side.

it is quite likely it will need to be 18 to 24 hours fasting to be sure my stomach is clear for the next endoscopy to all go successfully. it is not desirable to go through the sedation repeatedly within short amounts of time if it can be helped with side effects.

i tested out the pico prep and instead of taking 2 to 3 hours, because of my ultra slow metabolism took overnight to work. even a 12 hour fast might not be long enough to clear my stomach and will need to be looked into with gp, not don't need a third endoscopy.

the process of rescheduling endoscopy requires a gp re referral and have a midday appointment next thursday to sort it out and also pain relief not being able to use nsaid's during the lengthy fast 12hr minimum now and an empty stomach, requiring opioid analgesia.

my 2nd endoscopy has actually been scheduled on january 29, rather than later on in february, so will need to postpone with family going away interstate then to towards the middle of february and difficulties including needing a support worker to stay overnight.

this wisdom tooth i may possibly need to have out with an oral surgeon because of roots being close to the nerve and is a longer narrower tooth than the other 3 i had out. i can feel the rough texture with my tongue where my gum is cracking as it goes through.
because of fentanyl being long acting after the endoscopy, it makes taking other sedative prescription medications and over the counter sedating antihistamines used regularly more dangerous.

the over the counter version of naloxone in the form a nasal spray, narcan or nyxoid is very expensive about $50 for only a couple of doses but there are subsurdises available under the pbs to get it on a script.

it would help with controlling overcrowding in peak having some services terminating at robina they could even have some terminating at helensvale if there was stabling facilities built in the area and be intended for those using light rail.

with single track sections south of varsity lakes and a limited capacity some peak services could terminate at robina and go straight into the stabling yards for the morning peak, while other services go further south on the single track sections.

there should be a move to extend the heavy rail beyond varsity lakes even if it was only single track at first to tullabudgera then to elanora due to the cost of bridges over the rivers, but would have to make it double going down to coolangatta airport.

of the ultra potent opioids fentanyl at around 100 times oral morphine feels so much more powerful than being on the buprenorphine around 40 times oral morphine which is a much safer when used at higher doses, fentanyl is 2.5 times stronger.

the fentanyl is incredibly powerful with effects still felt 1-2 days later and had limited other pain relief yesterday due to lasting side effects, it was causing me to fall asleep during the middle of the day yesterday for several hours and a shorter time today.

in the lead up to the second endoscopy i'll use the pico prep to flush out my stomach and bowel with fentanyl causing nausea, bloating and severe constipation after the first endoscopy. i can get the pico prep from a pharmacist without a script, it is schedule 3.

the side effects from fentanyl have changed from the heavy sedation during and after the endoscopy to severe constipation and feeling very full. a gp script for naloxone and or targin is an option to reverse opioid induced constipation, in addition to laxatives.

because of the fentanyl being so potent they always require an anethesist to be present during the procedures. the drowsiness persists for longer with fentanyl than morphine, it has a similar feel to buprenorphine 40x, but is 2.5 times stronger 100x oral morphine.

the endoscopy was cleared to proceed but will need a second one in a month, because i didn't fast for long enough due to my slow metabolism and had constipation. i had a combination in the iv of midazolam, propofol and fentanyl which gave me a very deep sedation.
its been a bit over an hour and 40 minute wait though the waiting room has cleared up quite a bit since this morning when it was packed.

i saw the hepatologist who i see at the burke st clinic walk past in the endoscopy, gastroenterology area of the hospital. i am not sure if she also works within the day procedure endoscopy unit. some drs have dual speciality in gastroenterology and hepatology.

the wait could be up to a couple of hours or so to see everyone with the unit quite busy only 2 days into the new year. if the go ahead is given for the endoscopy discharge is around the early afternoon.

the wait in gastroenterology for the endoscopy can be quite lengthy and won't know for some time if it will go ahead with my tonsillitis still being present though mild now as i will have to wait until the dr can access it.

i saw  in king george square this morning on adelaide st when changing buses to go up to red hill cinema, it was quite packed being a public holiday, for the 4 gold rooms staff were stretched with food orders, but still got it eventually after delays.

i think vic is the same with s3 as nsw, in that i can remember in 2018 getting hydrozole cream in rosebud for my skin issues that did not have a label added. qld tends to be overregulated to a degree and similarly with alcohol not able to be sold in supermarkets.

in qld, due to the s3 labeling requirements, a move to reschedule panadol osteo and modified release paracetamol 665mg generics to schedule 3, will create more red tape around the sales in qld which is a bit excessive, but will have less impact in other states.

queensland certainly has stricter health regulations than nsw for pharmacies, schedule 2's don't have to be sold behind the counter in nsw, while schedule 3's don't require labeling in nsw (only s4 and s8 prescriptions), only that the pharmacist be consulted.
i was lucky to see that, i got a tick bite while camping out in the tent at a family property and have taken phenergan that will stop the sickness being felt after it so i can get to sleep now.
four different types of cough medicine used in addition to the antibiotics, the pe chesty seems to work best due to its decongestant action

i am now on erythromycin with the cough from my chest infection persisting for an extended time, the type of infection i have is resistant to penicillin, so failed to fully clear the infection on amoxicillin and only reduced the severity of my infection.

the clothesline got ripped from its socket at the other end, while a nearby lightening strike on a power pole cut power about 10:45pm last night. my laptop and phone had plenty of battery charge so didn't effect me that much.

lightening has caused a blackout in the mt gravatt area, my phone and computer have quite a long battery life so can go quite a while waiting for energex to fix the problem. thunder has been very loud for a while now.

in light of the scheduled endoscopy, i am now on the pseudoephedrine with the congestion not clearing enough with other less strong decongestants, whether in a nasal spray, cough liquid or tablets. pseudophedrine treats the swollen membranes in the nose.

the different style of edmr was required in relation to the upcoming endoscopy due to the handing of extremely severe trauma and a great volume of incidents of sexual abuse details involved, within less than two short years in 2004 and 2005, needing a black vision.

i have needed to use a different type of edmr, because of the endoscopy which is blackened out to the eye with a blindfold and not following the green dots left to right, but the vibration and audio are both still moving synchronized between left to right.

ketamine is also a powerful but non opioid pain reliever, so can be given via iv for post procedure pain relief. although it is not an opioid it is still a schedule 8 controlled drug due to misuse and addiction risk if used on a long term basis.

an anethesist will be present during the twighlight anaesthetic and will ask about using ketamine during the procedure, potentially for a deeper sedation and or to cause a trance or heavy amnesia with the endoscopy procedure being done.

with my endoscopy scheduled for january 2nd, emdr treatment today will be focusing on my sexual abuse incidents including the most severe gang rapes at autism queensland where i had forced oral sex and erect penis shoved down my throat.

i have just had my endoscopy scheduled early in the new year on thursday january 2nd, provided that my infection and severe chesty cough is cleared by then. the endoscopy procedure would need to be rescheduled if the infection persisted.

on the way home a lady on the 175 bus had a potential miscarriage bleeding on the bus floor and the service had to be abandoned at stones corner for an ambulance to arrive and got the next 174 service. it was a very confronting thing to see.

i've now seen a movie in three of the five cinemas at the new red hill cinema, in 1, 2 & 4. i always end up walking down to normanby busway station from the cinema as i have missed them on the other side of waterworks rd and takes to long to cross at the lights.
it is easier to exercise now with temperatures down and cloud cover. breeze is cooling at red hill also.

wilsons peak is similar to the cougals with the qld/nsw state border fence following the trail for most of the way. i can remember doing the cougal track, from garden of eden rd, late 2011 and a storm set in on the return to the car and got drenched in heavy rain.

wilsons peak, which has the qld/nsw border fence and over 1200 metres high is said to be the hardest of mountains to climb in the area with the steepest track and would be a class 5, although mt superbus and mt roberts are taller over 1300 metres in height.

my phone has a compass on it and not in an area with network coverage, it shows the coordinates of the position using the google map function from satellite. it could help in winter 2020, looking at doing a climb up mt superbus which is seq's highest mountain.

smaller pharmacies don't stock the pe chesty red labeled duro-tuss and had the gps on my phone find a chemist warehouse in the middle of ipswich on saturday and direct us onto the cunningham highway on the long drive out to queen mary falls.

the pe chesty, red label, duro-tuss is great for relief of chest and nasal congestion but does have a laxative effect waking up with diarrhea. i now have some otrivin plus nasal spray that is powerful and has a combination of a decongestant and antihistamine.

i have been a bit pressured with the next part of my submission to the , with the chair indicating finalising half of the 2020 schedule before the christmas summer break but should be able to get the 2nd part done in 2019 and a part 3 early on in 2020.

there was a particularly rough and rocky section in one creek crossing on condamine river rd that would normally have water flowing over it that a low clearance 2wd vehicle could get stuck on but otherwise the gravel road was in very good condition, few potholes.

after the walk in queen mary falls and seeing very limited water in the creek, a drive was taken down the 4wd condamine river rd and very little water around in the creek bed with the normally 14 crossings all dry. 4wd mode on the triton ute was never needed.

past the gap now the smoke has cleared up and a more pleasant drive west almost into warrick before turning off to head towards killarney. air conditioning had to be put on recycled air going through the bushfire smoke.
the bushfires have caused a lot of devestation going through cunningham's gap on route to queen mary falls with fires burning on the road sides. lots of thick smoke hazes.

the heat in the mid to high 30s feels particularly intense outside on the back wooden deck, with the surface hot enough to burn feet standing on the wood in bare feet to hang clothes out to dry, but are very quick to dry in the hot sun.

the 38° heat was tough walking from the new red hill cinemas down to the busway station at normandy where there was a 30 minute gap creating a long wait between 379, 380 and 381 services, a 2nd 379 service each hour is needed to get 15 minute frequency of services.

the 174 i was on came very close to colliding with a black bmw at greenslopes pulling out of the bus stop on logan rd with a car trying to turn left from the wrong lane. it was only millimetres short with the right side of the bus where i sat behind the driver.

i am now on antibiotics after getting some whooping cough symptoms, but the lyrica at high doses being an anti-convulsant works well to suppress the cough pattern, i got a cough medicine duro-tuss pe chesty from the pharmacy today that also clears nasal congestion.

i went for a walk in tamborine yesterday in the palm grove section, the jenyns circuit which is the longest of the walks in the national park, had some rough rocky sections that were challenging for my swollen ankles. it is at the lower end of the class 4 grading.

i have used nurofen plus before for irritable bowel syndrome before and is very effective, the codeine feels soothing on the gut with some mild constipation at low doses, while the ibuprofen heels an inflamed bowel.

i have had bleeding in the gut after using high dose ibuprofen for a long time due to my tendons and ankles also having arthritis in them. i'll likely have to go back on celebrex or nurofen plus with the codeine allowing a reduced dose of ibuprofen to be taken.

ankle pain is worst in the morning after anything taken the previous day has warn off and need to have a shower before i can use the mometasone lotion (zatamil) needing to let it dry on. the injury is more responsive to cortisone medication than nsaid's.

i have a psoriasis type of arthritis and mometasone has be rubbed into skin rashes and flaked skin on my legs and scalp. i have to apply on my foot an hour before any personal training session to give it time to work before i can put my shoes on without the pain.

i have been using mometasone the last couple of days before personal training sessions, it is a medium strength cortisone lotion on my ankles, due to the swelling pressing on the bone on top of my foot, making it harder and more painful to fit into my shoes.

it was the northern stairs on platform 1 at buranda that i injured my left ankle and strained the tendon close to the top trying to rush to the other side not knowing how much time i had to get the connecting service.

one of the lifts is out of order at buranda station, it has more stairs than average to cross over to the other side from a city bound bus to catch the 170 home. it is very hard on my ankles, hopefully the lift is fixed soon.

the shinbone is very strong so would take a much greater impact to be broken, it was sore for a couple of hours after the trip, but strains of the tendon are much easier to do tripping or landing hard, in 2008 i tripped on carpeted floor and did a similar strain.

the right is consistent with damage from getting a very hard landing around the back and under heel getting off the 175 bus while the shinbone took the most of the impact of the trip on the stairs at buranda busway station with some straining in my left tendon.

ultrasound has revealed damage to the soft tissue is worse in my right foot made worse by an arthritis condition, although the pain and swelling is more severe in my left being a more recent injury. i got a pbs script for high strength brufen or ibuprofen 400mg.

the decongestant has relieved some of the pressure and have started to feel clearer in the head, but an antihistamine like promethazine can be used to manage more serious symptoms to stop the histamine or the bodies immune response from becoming dangerous.

it is mainly lightheaded or dizziness and a bit disoriented with pressure in my sinuses that i have experienced since drinking the cup of hot chocolate with off milk, but no fever, nausea, vomiting, diarrhea or increasing pain levels as yet, i'll use some sudafed.

close to where i live a bulk billing dr attached to the local pharmacy has been available on sunday and booked an appointment for tomorrow to look at ultrasound results on my feet with the ongoing pain it has been causing, but may also need to be given antibiotics.

i had thought that i might have put the hot chocolate in the microwave for too long as it tasted strange like it was burnt, before i checked the milk and realized it was not drinkable. i now have to be prepared for a possible e coli or salmonella infection.

i inadvertently drunk hot chocolate with milk that had gone off and over a week past its use by date before i realized the whole 3l bottle was off and tipped the rest down the sink, but have started feeling a bit unwell and have to watch out for possible infection.

sporting carnivals inter-house like swimming and athletics and state high competing against other schools is where a lot of the emotion comes from after leaving , but for me it was more of a social structure that didn't continue into tafe and beyond.

the main thing that hasn't changed with the  graduation is how there is a lot of mixed emotions from being relieved to have the stress of exams and assignments over but some feelings would be sad, not getting to see each other in the same groups again.
back in 2011 the crowding outside the hall didn't take that long to clear probably only 15 minutes before it was clear to get graduation photos done when most of the crowd had gone.

it is certainly noticeable how large  is with crowding outside the exhibition hall which took much longer to disperse along with very long lines of students exiting down merivale st and they have to stage the exiting much more than just graduates.

the west end waterfront is nearly unrecognisable now, it was largely industrial along the river when i lived in this area, that has long gone and has been replaced by a lot of luxury waterfront apartments.
it is a great cooling breeze out on the water at milton city cat terminal after walking on the hot pavement from the clinic and now waiting to go up river.
there are many cafes and restaurants in this area in milton and there are high rise appartments are similar to those in west end or south brisbane that put pressure on the local catchment capacity .

i found the new psychiatry clinic with around 10 minutes to spare after walking around a bit to find where the entrance was to the correct lift. the single toilet at the clinic upstairs is marked as an all gender toilet.

the 170 overtook a late 174 at holland park and i can now leave later to get to milton instead of toowong, provided i catch the 170 to get into the inner city quickly, from holland park park and ride which is a bit more of walk than local stops.

the trip via city cat to west end from milton is only 11 minutes and can work my problem ankle in orleigh park on softer ground and have lunch at albertos and see down the street where i used to live. buses are very frequent into the central part of west end.

the inner city south secondary college won't be ready until 2021 for  to have a reduced catchment area, so 2020 would be a major test to control enrollment numbers not having the relief of a reduced grade size after 2019 that has existed since 2015.

after getting relief from enrollment pressures due the prep transition,  i can imagine it will be very difficult to get a student population less than 3300 in 2020 and if each grade had 600 each it could be as high as 3600. grade 9, i read it was 588.

normally the graduating class of grade 12s would get to leave first and are the smallest grades of the school due to the 2007 change with prep, but would expect to see quite a lot of push and shove from the other five grades trying to exit the exhibition hall.

after doing things in west end i'll get to see what  looks like later this afternoon with a student population in excess of 3000 coming out of the exhibition halls. i could clearly see everything from the other side of marivale st back in 2013.

i have a midday psychiatrist appointment today now in milton and easier access to get to both on the train or city cat, before i'll make my way to do some things in west end. i have a break in my edmr program this week but i resume with it next week.

the 2019  graduation ceremony today is notably later in the day (12:30 to 2:30pm) compared to the graduations in previous years, it was about 11pm to 1pm immediately after the morning tea break that finished at 11, from what i can remember in 2011.

the last year before year 7 commenced high school in 2015, 2014 was the year where the brisbane exhibition & convention centre was not available for the  graduation ceremony due to the g20 and was moved to the tennis centre in tennyson.

there should be limited appeals allowed for certain short suspensions from 5 to 10 days, on specific grounds in relation to student with a disability enrolled at a state school with a special education program or special school, with an overnight decision possible.

it is certain the current education general provisions act is discriminatory allowing exclusions to be imposed and remain on record for longer than is reasonably necessary to address a particular risk or behavior & 2 to 12 months is adequate for most exclusions.

had a decision been taken in 2002 to appeal the dutton park state school exclusion decision on the basis of education queensland getting my placement wrong, there would have been a compelling case if not for the exclusion overturned to get it reduced to 3-6 months.

education queensland should need to apply to qcat to extend an exclusion decision beyond 3 years and there should also be an appeal right for an external review to qcat after two consecutive rejections of annually allowed submissions to get an exclusion revoked.

this would be a needed safeguard in particular to remove disability discrimination, in 2010 i tried and failed after 8 years since my 2002 permanent exclusion from dutton park state school to get the exclusion decision expunged from my education queensland record.

legal restrictions on permanent exclusions under education general provisions act should exist to require that principals, regional directors or director-general must be satisfied that a risk or behavior would continue beyond 1 year, without a permanent exclusion.

permanent exclusions are in practice indefinite exclusions that can be reviewed each year, these have weakness and only for worst cases as they can make it harder to set reintegration strategies for resuming school compared to a fixed term of some months or a year.

that girl would be lucky to only get excluded from heatley state school, if the incident does not prompt a referral to the regional director or director-general to consider exclusion from certain state in the area or all state schools.
